nd wonderful.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nThe stars looked down at me from infinite space. We are tiny, they said, but you are insignificant.\n\n- Shane\n|\nEnlightenment is making every cell, gene and DNA as the radiator of peace and harmony.\n\n- Amit Ray, Enlightenment Step by Step\n|\nActualize the dreams now and don’t procrastinate them for the future. Use every second, minute and hour that you have to fulfill life’s calling, your purpose, and your dreams.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nI tell myself I am brave and yet, I still fear change. I guess it’s time to face that fear.\n\n- Avina\n|\nWhat does it mean to live in truth? Putting it negatively is easy enough: it means not lying, not hiding, and not dissimulating.\n\n- Milan Kundera, The Unbearable Lightness of Being\n|\nRun your own race of life, with a single minded vision of purpos\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nIf you want inner peace, unconditionally forgive everyone. If you want world peace, be an example and love everyone.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI am so tired of this gothic crap,” I muttered. “Just once, I want to meet the villain in a cheerful, brightly lit room. Possibly one with kittens.\n\n- Seanan McGuire, An Artificial Night\n|\nThe mud of this body-complex (pudgal - that which charges and disharges) is such that the harder one tries to get out, the deeper and deeper he sinks into it.\n\n- Dada\n|\nAbove all, trust in the slow work of God.\n\n- Pierre\n|\n...try to remember that dreams do come true, but they don't come easily.\n\n- Josephine Angelini, Dreamless\n|\nPeople are afraid of being more ignorant than their children―especially, apparantly, their daughters.\n\n- Daniel C. Dennett, Breaking the Spell: Religion as a Natural Phenomenon\n|\nPeople don't like getting older, but they do like changing\n\n- Tommy Wallach, Thanks for the Trouble\n|