d of the mind serving the systems.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Education Decree\n|\nTake you example by this thing,/ And yield to each his right,/ Lest God with such like miserye/ Your wicked minds requite\n\n- Various\n|\nAs you walk through forestsor the meadows of your mind,Stop and talk to those you fearGood friendships you may find\n\n- Stephen Cosgrove, Buttermilk Bear\n|\nHis tricks had raised the temperature of the room considerably, although I was pretty sure his presence alone had that effect.\n\n- Adele          Rose, Awakening\n|\nJesus girls! Wake up! If a guy wants to drain you of your energy, emotions, and life force he won’t sparkle in the sunshine, he’ll just marry you.\n\n- Nick\n|\nYou can build your strength, If you read enough books!\n\n- Lailah\n|\nSuch as make the sacrament only a representation of Christ do aim short of the mystery, and come short of the comfort.\n\n- Thomas Watson, The Lord's Supper\n|\nCall him Voldemort, Harry. Always use the proper name for things. Fear of a name increases fear of the thing itself.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone\n|\nIf we can become still and open-minded we might all feel that unseen hand on our shoulder, letting us know we are not alone.\n\n- June\n|\nI am the Atma abiding in the heart of all beings. I am also the beginning, the middle, and the end of all beings.\n\n- Anonymous, The Bhagavad Gita\n|\nJust above our terror, the stars painted this storyin perfect silver calligraphy. And our souls, too oftenabused by ignorance, covered our eyes with mercy.\n\n- Aberjhani, I Made My Boy Out of Poetry\n|\nHow can we stop learning, if we still have breath?\n\n- Lailah\n|\nOnly when we start to distinguish reality from fantasy that we can humbly, with eyes wide open, forge loving and sustainable connections with others.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg, Real Love: The Art of Mindful Connection\n|\nThe day I understood everything, was the day I stopped trying to figure everything out. The day I knew peace was the day I let everything go.\n\n- C.\n|\nTo carry each other’s burdens, we must care for one another.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nSunshine brings a new day,moonlight ends the harsh light.\n\n- Cara\n|\nThis funny thing we call love, how simple it may seem. To say it is sometimes enough but to feel it is a dream.\n\n- Raneem\n|\nI believe that God is in me as the sun is in the colour and fragrance of a flower - the Light in my darkness, the Voice in my silence.\n\n- Helen\n|\nTime and I have quarrelled. All hours are midnight now. I had a clock and a watch, but I destroyed them both. I could not bear the way they mocked me.\n\n- Susanna Clarke, Jonathan Strange & Mr Norrell\n|\nPlanning your day before it begins, and adjusting your plan through the day, is one of the most important daily habits.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, The Good Life: Transform your life through one good day\n|\nSo that's little Scorpious. Make sure you beat him in every test, Rosie. Thank god you've inherited your mother's brains.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows\n|\nIf we pray, we shall have peace,\n\n- Lailah\n|\nIf you want to continue to be the best in the world, then you have to train and compete like you are second best in the world.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all of Us: 12 Rules for Success\n|\nThe stares were annoying, but I knew they didn’t mean any harm. So, every morning, smiling at them became part of my routine, too.\n\n- Sarah Todd Hammer, Determination"